TRANSLA TIONS.

Dost thou look back· ?

DOST thou look back on what hath been, As some divinely—gifted man, Whose life in low estate began

And on a simple village green;

Who breaks his birth's invidious bar, And grasps the skirts of happy chance, And breasts the blows of circumstance,

And grapples with his evil star:

Who makes by force his merit known, And lives to clutch the golden keys, To mould a mighty state's decrees,

And shape the whisper of the throne:
